description:
Multi-band parametric equalizer with global bypass.

# Internal Type This is the internal representation using `Vec<EqualizerBand>`. API consumers work with band indices (1-based) via JSON paths like `/audio/output/speaker/1/user/eq/bands/3`.

# Band Counts by Layer - **User EQ**: 10 bands (user-adjustable) - **Array EQ**: 5 bands (installer tuning) - **Preset EQ**: 15 bands (factory presets)

# Structure - `bypass`: Master EQ bypass (affects all bands) - `bands`: Vector of `EqualizerBand` (internal indexing: 0-based, API: 1-based)

# Patch Behavior The `bands` field is marked `#[patch(skip)]` because bands are updated individually via `SetSpeakerOutputUserEqBand` requests, not as a complete array replacement.

# Usage Pattern ```ignore // Create 10-band user EQ let eq = Equalizer::create(10);

// Access band 3 (0-indexed internally) let band = &eq.bands[2];

// Client updates band 3 via API (1-indexed) // Path: /audio/output/speaker/1/user/eq/bands/3 ```
